<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1170571813852">
<term>integrating factor</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170571813858">any function <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> that is multiplied on both sides of a differential equation to make the side involving the unknown function equal to the derivative of a product of two functions</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170571813876">
<term>linear</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170571813882">description of a first-order differential equation that can be written in the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>′</m:mo></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>c</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170572386140">
<term>standard form</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170572386145">the form of a first-order linear differential equation obtained by writing the differential equation in the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>′</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
